-- Japan's Bonds Decline After Asian Development Bank Raises Growth Forecast
-- Yasuhiko Seki
-- 2010-07-20T04:56:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-19/japanese-government-bonds-may-advance-on-concern-global-economy-is-slowing.html

          
          
             Japanese  bonds  fell after the Asian
Development Bank raised its growth forecast for 2010, adding to
speculation recent gains in government debt were overdone.  
 The  yield  on the benchmark 10-year bond rose one basis
point to 1.095 percent as of 1:55 p.m. at Japan Bond Trading Co.,
the nationâ€™s largest interdealer debt broker. The 1.1 percent
security due June 2020 fell 0.090 yen to 100.044.  
 Ten-year bond futures for September delivery dropped 0.02
to 141.64 at the Tokyo Stock Exchange.  
